		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">James Burke (science historian)</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="dablink">For other persons named James Burke, see <a href="/wiki/James_Burke_(disambiguation)" title="James Burke (disambiguation)" class="mw-redirect">James Burke (disambiguation)</a>.</div>
<p><b>James Burke</b> (born 22 December 1936) is a <a href="/wiki/Northern_Ireland" title="Northern Ireland">Northern Irish</a> <a href="/wiki/Science" title="Science">science</a> <a href="/wiki/Historian" title="Historian">historian</a>, <a href="/wiki/Author" title="Author">author</a> and <a href="/wiki/Television_producer" title="Television producer">television producer</a> best known for his <a href="/wiki/Documentary_film" title="Documentary film">documentary</a> <a href="/wiki/Television_series" title="Television series" class="mw-redirect">television series</a> called <i><a href="/wiki/Connections_(TV_series)" title="Connections (TV series)">Connections</a></i>, focusing on the <a href="/wiki/History_of_science_and_technology" title="History of science and technology">history of science and technology</a> leavened with a sense of humour.</p>
